# Full-Stack Delivery Workflow

For **every change or feature request** in this repo, deliver a complete working slice — not a partial implementation.

## 1. Update all three layers

| Layer | Location | Check |
|-------|----------|-------|
| **DB** | `apps/api/src/database/entities/`, `tenant-seed.service.ts`, TypeORM entities | Schema/seed matches new fields; `STORAGE_MODE=postgres` paths persist correctly |
| **API** | `apps/api/src/modules/`, DTOs, `packages/types/` | Endpoints save and retrieve from DB (no in-memory-only business data) |
| **UI** | `apps/web/src/`, `apps/web/src/lib/api/endpoints.ts` | Pages/components call API; types from `@tms/types` stay in sync |

Shared types live in `packages/types/` — update there when API and UI share a shape.

## 2. Verify before finishing

- Build API: `cd apps/api && npm run build`
- Smoke-test the affected flow (create → read → update if applicable)
- Confirm data survives an API restart when persistence is involved
- Fix linter/type errors in touched files

## 3. Commit and push

After the feature works end-to-end:

1. `git status` + `git diff` — review all changed files
2. Stage relevant files (never `.env` secrets)
3. Commit with a clear message (why, not just what)
4. `git push` to remote

Do not leave completed feature work uncommitted.

## 4. Restart the app

```bash
# Kill old processes, rebuild API, start both
lsof -ti :3000 | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null
lsof -ti :3001 | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null
cd apps/api && rm -f tsconfig.tsbuildinfo && npm run build && npm run start
# In another terminal:
npm run dev:web
```

- API: http://localhost:3000
- Web: http://localhost:3001
- Postgres must be running when `STORAGE_MODE=postgres` (`npm run db:up` in `apps/api`)

## Ephemeral exceptions

Only these may stay in-memory: notification delivery queue, queue `servedToday` display counter. Everything else (devotees, bookings, donations, committees, check-ins, receipts) must use PostgreSQL.
